us imagination. Drawing from the deep well of love poetry, mythology, philosophy, and literature The Amorous Imagination comes to the provocative conclusion that without the productive power of the imagination love itself could not emerge.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aImagination (Philosophy). 0aLove in literature. 0aLovexPhilosophy. 0aPhenomenology. 4aLiterature : Romanticism. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Phenomenology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2021z978311149169140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848475440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438484754423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438484754/original  a978-3-11-149169-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles